This paper deals with the computation of credibility measures for predictions in a party-based election system. The paper uses computational complexity theory to analyze the problem of computing these measures for different scoring rules. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Computational Geometry and Topology), which deals with the computational aspects of game theory. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper involves the analysis of algorithms and their applications in social networks and decision-making processes.
